<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-461-540  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 461 540.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  May 22 1990 v7 n20 p31(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>E-mail tool converts files for seamless swapping. (ConsumersSoftware Inc introduces Network Courierpak) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Higgins, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Consumers Software Inc introduces Network Courierpak, a newrelease of its messaging system that combines its Network Courierelectronic mail software with Keypak, a word-processor filetranslation program licensed from Keyword Office Technologies Ltd.andO;Network Courierpak lets users of 35 popular IBM PC and Mac wordprocessors seamlessly exchange files in their native formats,automatically translating each to the recipient's native wordprocessing format.andP;  It saves both time and workstation memorybecause users do not have to learn multiple word processingprograms or translate documents with stand-alone utilities.andP;  Theprogram costs $2,490 per server; users of Consumers' InternetworkCourier wide-area network package can upgrade for $1,500 perserver.andP;  Consumers also sells the package from Keyword separatelyfor $200 per user.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Consumers Software Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Network Courierpak (Electronic mail system) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Electronic mail systemsProduct IntroductionFile ManagementData ConversionWord processingCompatibility.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Network Courier translates files into word-processing formats.andO;(chart)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Steve HigginsandM;Consumers Software Inc. last week extended the purview of its LAN E-mailsoftware with a new release that automatically translates attached filesamong most PC and many Mac word processors while performing its regularmessaging duties.andM;The Network Courierpak integrates Consumers' Network Courier messagingsoftware with the Keypak word-processor translator that Consumers licensedfrom Keyword Office Technologies Ltd.andM;The result is a package that enables users of 35 programs, ranging fromDisplayWrite to WordPerfect, to seamlessly swap files in their nativeformats, company officials said.andM;Each file is automatically translated to the recipient's nativeword-processing format as the user stores the file.andP;  Previously, a userexchanging dissimilar files would have to learn more than one word-processingprogram or translate the document locally with a stand-alone translationprogram.andM;Both methods require extra memory at each workstation and extra time for eachuser.andM;&quot;It's not realistic to expect those people to reach a level of expertise withtwo or three different word processors, and separate conversion programs arepretty grisly,&quot; said Greg Scott, computing services manager at Oregon StateUniversity's College of Business in Corvallis.andM;Scott, a beta tester of the new software, is using it to link Microsoft Wordand WordPerfect users.andM;When users install the new messaging program, they select a default wordprocessor into which all their text-mail attachments will be converted, Scottexplained.andP;  &quot;After that, they don't have to think about it,&quot; he said.andM;A user of Microsoft Word, for example, can read a mail attachment created inWordPerfect by saving the document to disk and calling up Word.andP;  The documenttranslation is done automatically as the document is stored, said MichaelShandrick, a spokesman for Consumers in Vancouver, British Columbia.andM;&quot;It's transparent,&quot; said George Prousalis, a systems analyst at DennisDavidson Associates Inc., a motion-picture public-relations firm.andM;Prousalis uses the Network Courierpak to connect users of three differentword processors in the company's offices in Los Angeles, New York, London,Paris, Milan and Sydney.andM;Prousalis added, however, that the program has limitations.andP;  &quot;It doesn't work100 percent because it can't convert all of the features of word processors,&quot;such as WordPerfect's ability to include graphics as part of a text document,he said.andM;Users of existing versions of Consumers' Internetwork Courier (for wide areanetworks) can upgrade for $1,500 per server.andP;  A Network Courierpak, includingNetwork Courier and three user-specified document translation formats, costs$2,490 per server.andP;  The Keyword package is also sold separately for $200 peruser.andM;Consumers Software Inc. can be reached at (604) 688-4548.andO;</TEXT></DOC>